08:03.100 --> 08:05.100
<i>Why did you stop, 123?</i>
<i>You got green ahead.</i>

08:05.300 --> 08:07.100
It's okay.

08:08.200 --> 08:10.300
Life is simple now.

08:10.500 --> 08:12.800
You just gotta do what I say.

08:17.600 --> 08:19.300
Not now, okay?

08:34.500 --> 08:35.700
Where are you from?

08:37.200 --> 08:39.500
- Brooklyn.
- You Irish?

08:40.100 --> 08:41.100
Yeah.

08:41.799 --> 08:43.900
I thought so.

08:44.900 --> 08:47.600
Who's driving Pelham 123?

08:51.400 --> 08:53.100
Maybe something fell on the tracks.

09:39.100 --> 09:41.200
Wait. Are we going backwards?

09:56.700 --> 09:59.100
42nd Street tower,
I got a train wrong-railing...

09:59.300 --> 10:02.200
...on the southbound Lexington
Avenue Line just north of you.

10:03.800 --> 10:06.600
Listen up,
we need to stop and stay in-station.

10:06.800 --> 10:09.900
All southbound locals
just north of the 51 st Street station.

10:10.100 --> 10:12.800
The operator on 123
is Jerry Pollard.

10:13.000 --> 10:15.900
I know Jerry Pollard.
I went to motorman school with Jerry.

10:16.100 --> 10:19.700
Pelham 123,
come in to me, Pelham 123.

10:19.900 --> 10:22.400
Pelham 123, Jerry Pollard,
what's going on down there?

10:22.500 --> 10:25.800
<i>This is Control Center.</i>
<i>What's going on, 123?</i>

10:28.000 --> 10:31.800
Get an express train to go alongside
them, see what we see in the cab.

10:31.900 --> 10:35.400
<i>Yeah, this is South Ferry 105. I can't</i>
<i>get my windshield wiper to turn on.</i>

10:35.600 --> 10:39.000
South Ferry 105, there's a circuit
breaker right behind you for that.

10:39.200 --> 10:40.500
What's going on?

10:40.700 --> 10:42.500
Maestro, what's going on?

11:00.000 --> 11:01.000
- Cop.
- Excuse me.

11:01.200 --> 11:03.600
